      <img src="/static8/us/2024/06/25/k-9-officer-dies-after-being-left-inside-hot-car.webp" alt="K-9 officer dies after being left inside hot car"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" >
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">K-9 officer dies after being left inside hot car</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The Savannah, Missouri police department confirmed on Monday that one of its K-9 officers died last Thursday after being left in a hot car overnight, KTLA sister station WDAF reported.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/us/2024/06/25/k-9-officer-dies-after-being-left-inside-hot-car/"  >(Olivia Johnson, KTLA 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 26 Jun 2024 03:19:10 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 26 Jun 2024 03:19:10 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/us/2024/06/26/judge-strikes-down-montana-law-defining-sex-as-only-male-or-female-for-procedural-reasons.webp" alt="Judge strikes down Montana law defining sex as only male or female for procedural reasons"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Judge strikes down Montana law defining sex as only male or female for procedural reasons</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      MISSOULA, Mont. (AP) — A judge on Tuesday struck down a Montana law that defined “sex” in state law as only male or female, finding that it was unconstitutional.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/us/2024/06/26/judge-strikes-down-montana-law-defining-sex-as-only-male-or-female-for-procedural-reasons/"  >(Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 26 Jun 2024 05:21:58 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 26 Jun 2024 05:21:58 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="JESSE BEDAYN, Associated Press, PHL 17">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/us/2024/06/26/boebert-faces-first-election-tuesday-since-switching-districts-and-the-vaping-scandal.webp" alt="Rep. Lauren Boebert wins GOP primary after switching Colorado districts; Hurd, Crank also notch wins"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Rep. Lauren Boebert wins GOP primary after switching Colorado districts; Hurd, Crank also notch wins</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      DENVER (AP) — U.S. Rep. Lauren Boebert won Tuesday's Republican primary in a U.S. House race that she jumped into last year, surviving a scandal over a video of her at a Denver theater and accusations of carpetbagging after fleeing what could have been a tough reelection bid in her current district.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/us/2024/06/26/boebert-faces-first-election-tuesday-since-switching-districts-and-the-vaping-scandal/"  >(JESSE BEDAYN, Associated Press, PHL 17)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 19 Jun 2024 16:01:17 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 19 Jun 2024 16:01:17 +0000">
