           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">California bill advances that would make Google, Facebook pay news companies whose stories appear on their platforms</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Researchers in a paper in November estimated Google gets about $21 billion a year, and Facebook about $4 billion a year, from news on their platforms.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/06/26/california-bill-advances-that-would-make-google-facebook-pay-news-companies-whose-stories-appear-on-their-platforms/"  >(Ethan Baron, The Mercury News)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
